<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920225-0164</DOCNO><DOCID>920225-0164.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Philadelphia Electric Co.:   Company Is Fined by NRC   For Safety Code Violations</HL><DATE>02/25/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A6</SO><CO>   PE</CO><MS>UTILITIES (UTI)</MS><IN>ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)NUCLEAR POWER, FUEL (NUK)EASTERN U.S. ELECTRIC UTILITIES (UEE)</IN><NS>NUCLEAR POWER, ENERGY (NUK)</NS><GV>FEDERAL GOVERNMENT (FDL)</GV><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)PENNSYLVANIA (PA)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Philadelphia Electric Co. has been fined $285,000 by theNuclear Regulatory Commission for several safety violationsat its Peach Bottom nuclear power plants located in Delta,Pa.   The violations involve the improper installation ofinsulation around several of the reactors' safety reliefvalves. The valves are part of a backup system used to lowersteam pressure in the reactor system in the case of certaincoolant leaks.</LP><TEXT>   A spokesman for Philadelphia Electric said the King ofPrussia, Pa., company has agreed to pay the fine, but addedthat the violations of NRC regulations never constituted ahazard to public safety. &quot;At no time was the plant in acondition that would have prevented a safe shutdown,&quot; thespokesman said. &quot;Over the past two years, progress was madeat improving the performance of the Peach Bottom plants.&quot;</TEXT></DOC>